What you may not have noticed is some new fees are taking a bite out of your savings. Some providers are applying additional fees (weekly admin fees and/or minimum program admin fees) adding up to 10 cents per gallon to your bill! Additionally, some of the “cents per gallon” rebates you may have seen may have been turned off by your card provider because of the falling fuel prices.


Flip over your next billing statement and look for headings that speak to “Minimum Program Administration Fee” and “Rebate/Volume Discount”.

